SPRINGBOK wing and 2019 Rugby World Cup final hero Cheslin Kolbe has been named Player of the Month in the French Top 14 following his superb performances for Toulouse. The 26-year-old wing made an impressive start to the new French Top 14 campaign and has been rewarded for the effort.The Top 14 announced on Monday that Kolbe bagged the most votes in the Player of the Month polls and congratulated the player for winning the award. Undoubtedly Kolbe will be a massive boost for Springbok head coach Jacques Nienaber if they play in next month's Rugby Championship in Australia, which gets underway on 7 November. #TOP14 #JoueurduMoisEt le Joueur du Mois @Paramourdurugby de Septembre est… Cheslin Kolbe ????L’ailier du @StadeToulousain a fait étalage de son talent en ce début de saison avec notamment un superbe doublé inscrit en J2.Bravo à lui et merci pour vos votes ! ?? pic.twitter.com/PukKXuOxYt  